    "折扣区"
  ],
  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "The lower half of a price range below the 50% Fibonacci equilibrium level, indicating undervaluation. In bullish contexts, it is the preferred zone for long entries, often confirmed by PD arrays like fair value gaps or order blocks. Price is expected to rebalance toward equilibrium when deviating into discount during consolidation.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Identify a significant swing high and swing low; apply Fibonacci retracement from swing high to swing low (using wick extremes if large wicks present).",
    "Plot the 0.5 Fibonacci equilibrium level; the area below this midpoint down to the swing low is the discount zone.",
    "Alternatively, use key reference levels such as midnight open (00:00 EST) and/or 8:30 AM (ET) open; price trading below these levels is in discount, with price below both indicating deep discount.",
    "For a tighter discount zone, narrow focus to the OTE range (0.62–0.79 Fibonacci retracement) within the lower half.",
    "Confirm the presence of a PD array (e.g., fair value gap, order block, breaker block, order block mean threshold) inside the identified discount zone.",
    "Only consider discount valid for long entries when the broader bias is bullish, confirmed by a prior market structure shift or change in state of delivery to the upside, often after a stop raid/liquidity sweep.",
    "Adjust the range by re-marking swing highs and lows as price action expands, since multiple nested ranges exist within a broader price section.",
    "In a bullish expansion, discount zones act as support; in a bearish expansion, a retracement into discount should be brief and fail to hold, with continued downside expected; failure to hold discount may signal a change in bias.",
    "When price trades outside the range low (deviation into discount), mark the new low-to-high leg and recalculate its own equilibrium to track the updated discount/premium boundaries."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "In a bullish market structure, discount zones below the 50% equilibrium serve as high-probability areas for long entries. Traders wait for price to retrace into discount and confirm with a PD array (e.g., order block, fair value gap) before entering. Entering deeper into discount improves risk-to-reward by reducing stop distance and targeting premium liquidity (e.g., previous day high, opposite range extreme). Stops are placed below the range low or swing low. In bearish expansions, discount retracements that fail to hold confirm continued downside. During consolidation, price deviating into discount is expected to rebalance back toward equilibrium.",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Entering long above the 0.5 equilibrium (in premium) instead of waiting for price to reach discount.",
    "Treating discount as a standalone entry signal without bullish bias, a prior market structure shift/stop raid, or a confirming PD array.",
    "Measuring the range from candle bodies instead of wick extremes, especially when large wicks are present.",
    "Failing to re-mark and adjust the range as new swing highs/lows form, leading to mismeasured equilibrium.",
    "Using a PD array located in the premium half of the range as a discount entry.",
    "Ignoring that discount/premium classification is bias-dependent; in bearish conditions, discount may not hold as support.",
    "Entering at an order block's opening price when a deeper retracement into discount could offer a tighter stop and better risk-to-reward.",
    "Continuing to apply the discount framework after a series of consecutive expansion candles, when price is likely transitioning into a new phase.",
    "Attempting to trade breakouts out of the range from discount instead of fading back into the range during consolidation conditions.",
    "Failing to recalculate discount/premium when price creates a new leg lower, missing the updated equilibrium level for the new range.",
    "Confusing discount as a directional signal (bullish bias) in all contexts rather than recognizing it as a reversion zone specific to consolidation/Seek and Destroy profiles.",
    "Buying in the discount zone without waiting for reversal confirmation (e.g., Change of Character, order block).",
    "Failing to adjust the Fibonacci tool as the impulsive wave expands, leading to misidentified zones.",
    "Entering too early in the discount zone and enduring a deeper retracement that stops out the trade.",
    "Assuming any retracement into the discount zone is a buy signal, ignoring the possibility of a trend reversal.",
    "Being overly conservative and waiting for price to reach deep discount levels, resulting in missed trades.",
    "将单一固定范围视为唯一参考，忽略价格走势中存在多个嵌套范围，导致折扣区判断混乱",
    "价格创新高后未同步上移范围高点，导致折扣区边界过时失效",
    "在折扣区内直接入场而不等待具体PD阵列（如Fair Value Gap或Order Block）的确认",
    "在下降趋势中，价格回撤至Discount区域时误判为多头机会，忽视更高时间框架的空头偏向",
    "未结合趋势方向使用Discount概念，孤立地将价格处于低位等同于适合做多",
    "在Premium区域的Order Block处寻找多头入场，忽视Discount/Premium的位置判断，导致入场合理性不足"
  ],
